{"article_id":"4vPK11srPlEx2Jap","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Four states are poised to cancel their 2020 GOP presidential primaries and caucuses , a move","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that would cut off oxygen to Donald Trump ' s long-shot primary challengers .","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"Republican parties in South Carolina , Nevada , Arizona and Kansas are expected to finalize the cancellations in meetings this weekend ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"according to three GOP officials","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"who are familiar with the plans .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"The moves are the latest illustration of Trump ' s takeover of the entire Republican Party apparatus .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"They underscore the extent","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"to which his allies are determined to snuff out any potential nuisance en route to his renomination","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"- or even to deny Republican critics a platform","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"to embarrass him .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"Trump advisers are quick to point out","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"that parties of an incumbent president","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"seeking reelection","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"have a long history","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"of canceling primaries","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"and note","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"it will save state parties money .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"But the president ' s primary opponents ,","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"who have struggled to gain traction ,","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"are crying foul ,","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"calling it part of a broader effort","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"to rig the contest in Trump ' s favor .","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"\" Trump and his allies and the Republican National Committee are doing whatever they can do","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"to eliminate primaries in certain states","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"and make it very difficult for primary challengers to get on the ballot in a number of states , \"","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"said former Rep. Joe Walsh","depth":13},{"id":26,"text":"( R-Ill. ) ,","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"who recently launched his primary campaign against the president .","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"\" It ' s wrong ,","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"the RNC should be ashamed of itself ,","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"and I think","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"it does show that Trump is afraid of a serious primary challenge","depth":14},{"id":32,"text":"because he knows","depth":15},{"id":33,"text":"his support is very soft . \"","depth":15},{"id":34,"text":"\" Primary elections are important ,","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"competition within parties is good ,","depth":16},{"id":36,"text":"and we intend to be on the ballot in every single state","depth":16},{"id":37,"text":"no matter what the RNC and Trump allies try to do , \"","depth":15},{"id":38,"text":"Walsh added .","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"\" We also intend to loudly call out this undemocratic bull on a regular basis . \"","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"Former Massachusetts Gov . Bill Weld said in a statement ,","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"\" We don ' t elect presidents by acclamation in America .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Donald Trump is doing his best","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"to make the Republican Party his own personal club .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"Republicans deserve better . \"","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"RNC officials said","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"they played no role in the decisions .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"The cancellations stem in part from months of behind-the-scenes maneuvering by the Trump campaign .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"Aides have worked to ensure total control of the party machinery ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"installing staunch loyalists at state parties","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"while eliminating potential detractors .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"The aim ,","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Trump officials have long said ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"is to smooth the path to the president ' s renomination","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"and ensure","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"he doesn ' t face the kind of internal opposition","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"that hampered former President George H.W . Bush in his failed 1992 reelection campaign .","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"Trump aides said","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"they supported the cancellations","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"but stressed","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"that each case was initiated by state party officials .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"The shutdowns aren ' t without precedent .","depth":5},{"id":62,"text":"Some of the states","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"forgoing Republican nomination contests","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"have done so during the reelection bids of previous presidents .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"Arizona ,","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"GOP officials there recalled ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"did not hold a Democratic presidential primary in 2012 ,","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"when Barack Obama was seeking a second term ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"or in 1996 ,","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"when Bill Clinton was running for reelection .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"Kansas did not have a Democratic primary in 1996 ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"and Republican officials in the state pointed out","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"that they have long chosen to forgo primaries during a sitting incumbent ' s reelection year .","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"South Carolina GOP Chairman Drew McKissick noted","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"that his state decided not to hold Republican presidential primaries in 1984 ,","depth":14},{"id":76,"text":"when Ronald Reagan was running for reelection ,","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"or in 2004 ,","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"when George W. Bush was seeking a second term .","depth":14},{"id":79,"text":"South Carolina ,","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"he added ,","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"also skipped its 1996 and 2012 Democratic contests .","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"\" As a general rule ,","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"when either party has an incumbent president in the White House ,","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"there ' s no rationale","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"to hold a primary , \"","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"McKissick said .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"Perhaps the closest comparison to the present day is 1992 ,","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"when George H.W . Bush was facing a primary challenge from conservative commentator Pat Buchanan .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Several states that year effectively ditched their Republican contests ,","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"including Iowa ,","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"which has long cast the first votes of the presidential nomination battles .","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"Buchanan said in an interview","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"that the cancellations overall played little role in his eventual defeat ,","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"adding","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"that Bush won renomination \" fair and square . \"","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"But Buchanan said","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"he was rankled by what he described as a concerted and ultimately successful GOP-led effort","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"to prevent him from appearing on the South Dakota ballot .","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"Buchanan said","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"he felt confident","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"that he could perform strongly in the conservative state ,","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"whose contest came just days after a New Hampshire primary","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"that he performed surprisingly well in .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"Not being able to compete there crushed him ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"Buchanan said .","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"\" If you think","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"you can ' t fight city hall ,","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"try overthrowing the president of the United States , \"","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"Buchanan said .","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"Officials in several states said in statements","depth":5},{"id":111,"text":"provided by the Trump campaign","depth":5},{"id":112,"text":"that they were driven by the cost savings .","depth":4},{"id":113,"text":"State parties in Nevada and Kansas foot the bill","depth":6},{"id":114,"text":"to put on caucuses .","depth":6},{"id":115,"text":"\" It would be malpractice on my part to waste money on a caucus","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"to come to the inevitable conclusion","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"that President Trump will be getting all our delegates in Charlotte , \"","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"said Nevada GOP Chairman Michael McDonald .","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"\" We should be spending those funds","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"to get all our candidates across the finish line instead . \"","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"Kansas GOP Chairman Michael Kuckelman estimated","depth":5},{"id":122,"text":"it would cost his party $ 250,000","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"to hold the caucus , money","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"he said","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"can be deployed","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"to win races .","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"Trump aides have long said","depth":3},{"id":128,"text":"they aren ' t worried about a primary challenge","depth":4},{"id":129,"text":"and laughed off his Republican challengers .","depth":4},{"id":130,"text":"But the president ' s political team has pored over past primary results","depth":3},{"id":131,"text":"and is mindful","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"that unexpected things can transpire -","depth":5},{"id":133,"text":"such as in 2012 ,","depth":5},{"id":134,"text":"when a federal inmate received 41 percent of the vote against Obama in the West Virginia Democratic primary .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":269,"left":261,"right":268,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"